Package: PeakSegPipeline
Type: Package
Title: Genome-Wide Peak Calling Using PeakSegFPOP and PeakSegJoint
Version: 2017.08.11
Author: Toby Dylan Hocking
Maintainer: Toby Dylan Hocking <toby.hocking@r-project.org>
Description: Implementations of supervised machine learning
 algorithms for peak detection in ChIP-seq data.
 PeakSegFPOP <arXiv:1703.03352> for single-sample peak calling
 (independantly for each sample and genomic problem).
 PeakSegJoint <arXiv:1506.01286>
 for joint peak calling (for each peak, jointly using all samples).
License: GPL-3
SystemRequirements: db_stl, bedGraphToBigWig, bigWigToBedGraph, bedToBigBed
Depends: R (>= 2.10)
Imports: data.table (>= 1.9.8), PeakError, PeakSegJoint (>= 2017.08.08),
 penaltyLearning, ggplot2, namedCapture, animint, xtable, WeightedROC,
 parallel, scales
Suggests: testthat, httr
